eruniface_104awm1665702727177.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awm1665702727177.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awm1665702727177.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"awm1665702727177\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n DB2 Data Packing\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"awm1665702727177__dbdata_packing_149636\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface data types and packing codes are mapped to DB2 storage formats.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"awm1665702727177__p_d49082e1_d49083e1_d49084e1\">For more information on Unicode data packing, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrl1665702727249.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrl1665702727249.html\" title=\"When Unicode is enabled, Uniface W and C packing codes can contain Unicode characters. The precise mapping and the number of Unicode characters that a field can contain depend on whether the DB2 database was created to use Unicode (UTF-8 encoding) or not (a code page).\">Unicode Packing Codes</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"awm1665702727177__table_d4667e1_d4668e1_d4669e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Mappings Between Uniface Packing Codes and DB2 Storage Format</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"awm1665702727177__table_d4667e1_d4668e1_d4669e1__entry__1\">\n Uniface Packing Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"awm1665702727177__table_d4667e1_d4668e1_d4669e1__entry__2\">\n DB2 Storage Format\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"awm1665702727177__table_d4667e1_d4668e1_d4669e1__entry__1\">\n B1-B4\n </t